CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 13, 1960, pg. 28 reads: "Happy Couple - Ernie Banks and his wife Eloyce, were guests in Pittsburgh over the weekend for the Dapper Dan banquet. Mrs. Banks, who has been doing a lot of traveling with the National League's most valuable player this winter, also will accompany Ernie to spring training this year. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Ernie Banks and wife Eloyce Banks wearing dark dress and light colored fur scarf, standing behind table with suitcase in interior
